# Office Hours Planner - Metaprompt

You are helping develop the **Office Hours Planner**: a frontend-only education web app (React + TypeScript + Vite) with Google Sheets (and optional Apps Script) as persistence. Auth is school-email only (`@mta.ca`, `@umoncton.ca`). No custom long-running backend. For full constraints, reasoning order, and deliverables, read [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) first.

## Key Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/App.tsx` | Root UI, session state, `loadCoreData` (classes/polls/slots/bookings), teacher vs student branches, all main handlers |
| `src/services/datastore.ts` | `DataStore` interface; `LocalDataStore` (localStorage + seed); `AppsScriptDataStore` (POST to script); `normalizePerson` (sheet row to Person with `courseIds`) |
| `src/services/auth.ts` | Session (localStorage); `signInWithPerson`, `getSessionUser`, `updateSession`; session has `myCourses` from `person.courseIds` |
| `src/types.ts` | `Person`, `SessionUser`, `ClassMembership`, `OfficeHoursPoll`, `PollResponse`, etc. |
| `src/config.ts` | `appConfig`: `allowedDomains`, `appsScriptUrl`, `appName` from env |
| `src/services/notifications.ts` | `NotificationSender`, `sendAnnouncement`; currently Apps Script or no-op |

## Data Flow (course dropdown, polls)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  subgraph auth [Auth]
    Login[Login with email]
    Person[getPersonByEmail]
    Session[SessionUser with myCourses]
    Login --> Person --> Session
  end
  subgraph teacher [Teacher UI]
    ListClasses[listClasses email]
    GetByIds[getClassesByIds myCourses]
    Classes[classes state]
    ListClasses --> Classes
    GetByIds --> Classes
  end
  subgraph ui [UI]
    Dropdown[Course dropdown]
    Classes --> Dropdown
  end
  Session --> ListClasses
  Session --> GetByIds
```

- **Teachers:** `classes` from `listClasses(effectiveUser.email)`; if empty, fallback `getClassesByIds(effectiveUser.myCourses)`. Backend must support one of: (1) `listClasses(email)` returns that teacher's classes, or (2) `getPersonByEmail` returns `courseIds` or `course1`–`course4` so `myCourses` is set.
- **Students:** Polls and classes from `listPollsForStudent(myCourses)` and `getClassesByIds(myCourses)`; `Person.courseIds` must be populated.
- **Normalization:** Apps Script may return `course1`..`course4` instead of `courseIds`. Frontend normalizes in `normalizePerson()` in datastore.ts.

## Backend Contract (Apps Script)

Single POST; body `{ action: string, ...payload }`. Actions: `getPersonByEmail`, `getClassesByIds`, `listClasses`, `listPolls`, `listPollsForStudent`, `createPoll`, `savePollResponse`, `suggestTopConfigs`, `saveOfficeHoursConfig`, `listSlots`, `createBooking`, `listBookings`, `saveAnnouncement`, `sendAnnouncementEmail`.

**Critical for course dropdown:** `getPersonByEmail` must return `courseIds` (array) or `course1`, `course2`, `course3`, `course4` (strings). `listClasses(email)` should return classes where `teacherEmail === email`.

## Constraints (do not break)

- Auth: only allowed domains; role and courses from Person/Sheets.
- No long-running backend; persistence is Sheets + optional Apps Script.
- One notification abstraction; email now, SMS pluggable later.
- Polls course-scoped; booking = one concrete slot per student; one office-hours poll per course.

## Common Pitfalls

- **Empty course dropdown for teachers:** Usually (1) Apps Script `listClasses(email)` returns `[]` or (2) `getPersonByEmail` does not return `courseIds` or `course1`–`course4`. Fix: ensure script returns course info and/or implements `listClasses` correctly.
- **LocalDataStore:** `listClasses(email)` filters by `teacherEmail === email`; seed data has `DEFAULT_CLASSES` and `SEED_PEOPLE` with matching `courseIds` / `teacherEmail`.
